<title>USA: Service Merchandise to shift $4 mln ad cost.</title>
<headline>Service Merchandise to shift $4 mln ad cost.</headline>
<dateline>NASHVILLE, Tenn. 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Service Merchandise Co Inc said Tuesday it expects to shift about $4 million, on an after-tax basis, of advertising expenses that were incurred in last year's fourth quarter into the third quarter this year.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to launch a television and insert advertising campaign in the third quarter directed towards placing a greater emphasis on new customers.</p>
<p>The company reported a second quarter share loss of $0.18 compared with a loss of $0.02 for the same period a year ago.</p>
